transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Hi, I've hurt my lower back at the gym yesterday. Can I book an appointment to see a physio?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Hi Sarah! Sorry to hear about your back injury. I can definitely help you book an appointment. We have availability tomorrow at 2:30pm or Thursday at 10am. Which works better for you?

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Thursday 10am would be perfect. What should I expect for the first appointment?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Great! I've booked you in for Thursday 10am with Dr. James. The initial consultation is 45 minutes and includes assessment, diagnosis, and treatment plan. Please bring any relevant medical history or scans if you have them.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Hi, could you please tell me your consultation fees? I'm looking for treatment for tennis elbow.

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Hi Michael! Our consultation fees are $120 for initial appointment (45 mins) and $95 for follow-up sessions (30 mins). Tennis elbow typically requires 4-6 sessions for full recovery. Do you have private health insurance?

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Yes I have Medibank Private. What's the gap payment?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: With Medibank you'll typically get $35-45 back per session, so your gap would be around $75-85 per visit. Would you like to book an assessment?

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Hi! Just wanted to update you on my shoulder progress after last week's session. The exercises are really helping!

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: That's wonderful to hear Emma! I'm so glad the exercise program is working well for you. How's the pain level compared to last week?

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Much better! Pain has gone from 7/10 to about 3/10. Should I continue with the same exercises?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Excellent progress! Yes, continue with the current exercises for another week. Dr. Sarah wants to see you next Tuesday to progress your program to the next level.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Perfect! Can we book the same time - 4pm?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Absolutely! I've got you down for Tuesday 4pm with Dr. Sarah. Keep up the great work with your exercises!

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: I've developed neck pain from working at a computer all day. It's been getting worse over the past month. Do you treat workplace injuries?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Hi David, yes we absolutely treat workplace-related injuries. Neck pain from prolonged computer work is very common. We can assess your posture, provide treatment, and give you ergonomic advice.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: That sounds exactly what I need. How soon can I get an appointment? The pain is affecting my sleep now.

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Given that it's affecting your sleep, I can fit you in tomorrow at 1pm for an urgent consultation. We'll also provide you with some immediate pain relief strategies.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Thank you so much! Tomorrow 1pm works perfectly.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Hi, I had ACL reconstruction surgery 6 weeks ago and my surgeon has cleared me to start physio. Do you have experience with post-surgical rehab?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Hi Jessica! Yes, we have extensive experience with ACL reconstruction rehabilitation. Dr. Mark specializes in post-surgical orthopaedic recovery. Do you have your surgeon's rehab protocol?

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Yes, I have all the paperwork from my surgeon. When can we start?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: We can start as early as Monday. I'll book you with Dr. Mark at 11am. Please bring your surgical notes and any imaging. ACL rehab typically takes 4-6 months, so we'll create a comprehensive program for you.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Do you offer group exercise classes or is it just individual treatment?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Hi Robert! We offer both individual physiotherapy sessions and group clinical pilates classes. Our group classes run Monday, Wednesday, and Friday evenings and are great for injury prevention and general fitness.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: What's the cost for the group classes?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: $35 per class or $150 for a 5-class pass. You can drop in anytime, but I'd recommend an initial assessment first to ensure the exercises are suitable for you.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: I'm a runner and I've been getting shin splints. Training for City2Surf in August - can you help me get back to running safely?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Absolutely Lisa! Shin splints are very common in runners and definitely treatable. We can assess your running biomechanics, provide treatment, and modify your training program to get you ready for City2Surf.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: That sounds perfect. I'm worried about losing my fitness if I stop running completely.

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Don't worry, we rarely recommend complete rest for runners. We'll likely modify your training with cross-training options and gradual return to running. Can you come in Friday afternoon?

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: I've had chronic lower back pain for 2 years now. Seen multiple doctors but nothing seems to help long-term. Do you think physio might be different?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Hi Kevin, I understand your frustration with chronic pain. Physiotherapy takes a different approach focusing on movement, strengthening, and pain education. Dr. Emma specializes in chronic pain management using evidence-based techniques.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: I'm willing to try anything at this point. How long does treatment usually take?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Chronic pain treatment varies, but we typically see improvements within 4-6 weeks with our comprehensive approach. Let's book you with Dr. Emma for a thorough 60-minute assessment next week.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Dear Physio Team, I hope this email finds you well. I'm experiencing persistent shoulder pain that's been affecting my work productivity. Could you please provide information about your assessment process and availability?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Hi James, Thank you for your email. I'm sorry to hear about your shoulder pain affecting your work. We'd be happy to help with a comprehensive shoulder assessment. Our next available appointment is Wednesday at 3pm with Dr. Sarah, who specializes in workplace-related injuries.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: That sounds perfect. Could you please send me the intake forms beforehand? I'd like to complete them prior to the appointment to save time.

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Absolutely! I'll email you the intake forms this afternoon. Please bring any relevant medical history or imaging results. We'll see you Wednesday at 3pm. Best regards, Reception Team

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Hey! Can I book a physio appt for next week? Hurt my ankle playing netball

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Hi Michelle! Sure thing - netball ankle injuries are common. We have Tuesday 11am or Thursday 2pm available next week. Which suits you better?

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Tuesday 11am works great! Thanks 👍

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Perfect! You're booked in Tuesday 11am with Dr. Mark. Address: 123 Physio St, Sydney. See you then! 😊

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Good morning, We are enquiring about corporate physiotherapy services for our office of 150 employees in Sydney CBD. Could you provide information about on-site services, group sessions, and corporate rates?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Good morning, Thank you for your corporate enquiry. We offer comprehensive workplace physiotherapy including on-site consultations, ergonomic assessments, and group education sessions. Our corporate packages start from $180 per employee per session with volume discounts available.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: That sounds very interesting. Could we arrange a consultation to discuss a tailored package for our organization? We're particularly interested in preventive care and ergonomic assessments.

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Absolutely! I'll arrange for our Corporate Health Manager to contact you within 24 hours to discuss a customized solution. Thank you for considering our services. Kind regards, Sydney Physio Team

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Hi! Just wanted to say thanks for the great session yesterday. Knee is feeling much better already! 🙌

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: That's fantastic to hear Tom! Really pleased the treatment is helping. Remember to keep up with those exercises we discussed.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Will do! Should I book the next session for next week?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Yes, let's keep the momentum going. Same time next Thursday work for you? I'll send a booking confirmation shortly.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Hey! Saw your running injury post on Instagram 🏃‍♂️ I'm training for Sydney Marathon and getting some IT band issues. Do you specialize in runner injuries?

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Hi Alex! Thanks for reaching out via Instagram! Yes, we absolutely specialize in running injuries - IT band syndrome is super common in marathon training. We can definitely help optimize your training load and address the biomechanics.

transcript.speaker: patient
transcript.text: Amazing! Marathon is in 4 months, need to stay on track with training 💪

transcript.speaker: staff
transcript.text: Perfect timing! 4 months gives us plenty of room to fix this and get you marathon-ready. Can you DM us your phone number? We'll call to book you in for a running assessment 🎯
